    "body": "## Problem\n\n```\nvim.schedule callback: /Users/x/dev/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:893: Invalid 'group': 'nvim.lsp.completion_8'\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_get_autocmds'\n\t/Users/x/dev/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:893: in function 'callback'\n\t/Users/x/dev/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:593: in function 'handler'\n\t/Users/x/dev/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:733: in function 'fn'\n\t/Users/x/dev/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/_core/editor.lua:274: in function </Users/x/dev/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/_core/editor.lua:273>\nvim.schedule callback: /Users/x/dev/neovim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:893: Invalid 'group': 'nvim.lsp.completion_8'\n```\n\n## Steps to reproduce\n\ndon't have minimal steps yet, but this error shouldn't happen regardless of steps.\n\n```\nnvim --clean\n\" edit lsp-enabled buffer\n\" invoke omnicompletion\n<c-x><c-o>\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\n\n## System info\n\n- Nvim version (nvim -v): `v0.12.0-dev-2541 g2ef6b6229f36` neovim/neovim@2ef6b6229f36\n- Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?: ?\n- Operating system/version: Darwin 24.6.0\n- Terminal name/version: ghostty 1.3.0\n- $TERM environment variable: `xterm-ghostty`\n- Installation: ?\n\n",
